                  <pb facs="#f042">f.41</pb>
                  <milestone facs="#f042_z000" n="41" unit="folio_number"></milestone><br>However<span class="addition">,</span> I do not wish to dwell any<br> further upon individual instances. Personal<br><milestone facs="#f042_z002" unit="guiding_line"></milestone> <span class="addition">experience </span>is a most vicious and limited circle. <br>All that I desire to point out is<br> the general principle that <span class="deletion">L</span><span class="addition"><span class="deletion">l</span></span><span class="addition">L</span>ife imitates<br> <span class="deletion">A</span><span class="addition"><span class="deletion">a</span></span><span class="addition">A</span>rt far more than <span class="deletion">A</span><span class="addition"><span class="deletion">a</span></span><span class="addition">A</span>rt imitates <span class="deletion">L</span><span class="addition"><span class="deletion">l</span></span><span class="addition">L</span>ife,<br> and I feel sure that if you think<br> seriously about it you will find<br> that it is true. <span class="deletion">Art </span><span class="addition"><span class="deletion">L</span></span><span class="addition"><span class="deletion">l</span></span><span class="addition">L</span><span class="addition">ife</span> holds the mirror<br> up to <span class="deletion">A</span><span class="addition"><span class="deletion">a</span></span><span class="addition">A</span>rt, and either reproduces <span class="deletion">the </span>some<br> strange type <span class="addition">imagined by</span> 
