                     <hi rend="italic">ivian.</hi></span> Briefly<span class="addition">,</span> then<span class="addition">,</span> 
                  <milestone facs="#f054_z008" unit="caret"></milestone><span class="addition">they </span>are these. Art<br> never expresses anything but itself.<br> It has an independent life, just <br>as Thought has, and develops purely<br> on its own lines. It is not necessarily <br>realistic in an age of realism,<br> nor spiritual in an age of faith.<br> So far from being the creation of<br> its time, it is usually in direct<br> opposition <span class="deletion">it </span>to it, and the only<br> history that it preserves for us<br> is the history of its own progress.<br> <span class="deletion">Art </span><span class="deletion">s</span><span class="addition">S</span>ometimes 
