                  <milestone facs="#f055_z000" n="53" unit="folio_number"></milestone><br>from the art of a time to the time<br> itself is the great <span class="deletion">fallacy of </span><span class="addition">mistake that </span>all<br> historians <span class="addition">commit</span>.<note rend="small">147</note> <br></p>
               					
               <p>The second doctrine is this. All bad<br> art comes from <span class="deletion">[?] </span>returning to <span class="deletion">L</span><span class="addition"><span class="deletion">l</span></span><span class="addition">L</span>ife<br> and <span class="deletion">N</span><span class="addition"><span class="deletion">n</span></span><span class="addition">N</span>ature, and elevating them<br> into ideals. Life and <span class="deletion">N</span><span class="addition"><span class="deletion">n</span></span><span class="addition">N</span>ature may 
