               <p>The third doctrine is that Life<br> imitates Art far more than Art <br>imitates Life. This results not merely<br> from Life's imitative instinct, but<br> from the fact that the <span class="deletion">desire </span><span class="addition">self-conscious aim</span> of Life<br> is to find expression, and that<br> Art
